verbose_text: Pore closure detected with spot F 647 bleaching by strong excitation is not due to a narrow pore smaller than A532 molecule size, because after spot dimming, bath application of an acid solution cannot quench the pH sensitive VAMP2-EGFP or VAMP2-pHluorin overexpressed at the same spot, indicating that the spot is impermeable to H+ or OH-, the smallest molecules, and thus is closed.
